title: r/Entitledparents "Your Baby Is Prettier Than Mine... Let Me Buy It!"
description:
r/Entitledparents In today's episode, a mother goes completely nuts and starts acting like her adult, 23-year-old daughter is her property. When the daughter goes to live with her boyfriend, the mom flips out and calls the cops on her, saying that she ran away from home. The cops arrive, and the police officer is shocked that the woman called the police on a 23-year-old woman running away from home!
